-- Chelsea to Play Monterrey in Club World Cup Semis; Al-Ahly Wins
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-12-09T14:28:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-12-09/chelsea-to-play-monterrey-in-club-world-cup-semis-al-ahly-wins.html
Mexican club Monterrey beat  South
Korea ’s Ulsan Hyundai 3-1 today to set up a semifinal against
European soccer champion Chelsea at the  Club World Cup  in Japan.  Cesar Delgado got two goals, while Jesus Corona also scored
for Monterrey in Toyota. It will face Champions League winner
Chelsea in Yokohama on Dec. 13.  Egypt’s Al-Ahly also advanced following a 2-1 victory
against Japanese club Sanfrecce Hiroshima. It faces Corinthians
of Brazil on Dec. 12 in Toyota.  Chelsea is aiming to give Europe a sixth straight title at
the annual competition, which is contested by the champions of
each continent’s soccer federation. Sanfrecce Hiroshima also
qualified this year as winner of the host nation’s J League.  The final is on Dec. 16.  To contact the reporter on this story:
 James Cone  in London at   jcone@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editors responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 